description: The UC Davis University Honors Program (UHP) provides students with an enriched undergraduate education through a small, liberal arts college setting, coupled with the resources and opportunities of a large world-class research university. During the first two years of the program students take small, interactive classes with select Honors faculty. In their third year students focus on community service, project-based learning, and preparing themselves to do research. In their fourth and final year students complete either an Honors Thesis or Capstone Project, as well as present their capstone research at a conference.
title: UC Davis University Honors Program
